{"id": "q039", "question": "What prevents the same dependency from being called twice within a single request, and how is the cache keyed?", "type": "cross-file", "relevant_files": ["dependencies/utils.py", "types.py"], "relevant_symbols": ["solve_dependencies", "DependencyCacheKey"], "reference_answer": "solve_dependencies maintains a dependency_cache keyed by DependencyCacheKey (callable + security scopes, defined in types.py); a cached result is reused instead of re-calling."}
